g.title: 工作表.72
g.desc: Description: P_ED[1:0]: if this record is the first record of...
g.text: Description:· P_ED[1:0]: if this record is the first record of a node, then set P_ED[1:0] = 2'b10; otherwise set P_ED[1:0] = 2'b00;· CTRL is exist only in the first record owned by the node; otherwise CTRL is RES0;· P_IS_ECC[31:0]: 1 means it is ecc error; · P_IS_UEU[31:0]: 1 means it is unrecoverable error;· P_IS_POIS[31:0]: 1 means it is poison error which comes from external;· in one record, there are 32 input errors and 1 corrected error with a counter;· SERR: the priority of errors are ECC>Implementation_defined_error>poison>corrected_error; SERR will be overwrited by higher priority.· UET: only support UEU and UER, the priority of UEU is higher than UER, so UEU could overwrite UER.· when poison error happen, set PN=1· when uncorrected error happen, set UE=1· when overflow error happen, set OF=1· SERR、UET、PN、V、UE、OF、MV can be update by hardware when fault=1· set CE=1 when plus_f=1· the priority of software is higher than hardware· STATUS_0, MISC0_0, MISC0_1, ADDR_0, ADDR_1 and MISC3_1 form a snapshot group. Accessing STATUS_0 will trigger a snapshot.
